1
00:01:35,479 --> 00:01:36,610
A couple of days ago,

2
00:01:36,960 --> 00:01:38,840
the ships didn't even dare to dock.

3
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:41,920
You had to take a small boat to the middle of the river to board.

4
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:42,680
Now,

5
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:44,720
taking a small boat to the middle of the river

6
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:45,920
costs thirty yuan.

7
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:47,320
Thirty yuan?

8
00:01:48,240 --> 00:01:48,880
Isn't that almost

9
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:49,680
one gold bar?

10
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:50,680
Exactly.

11
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:52,009
I'm telling you,

12
00:01:52,039 --> 00:01:53,300
that's today's price.

13
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:53,960
Tomorrow,

14
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,530
who knows how high it'll go.

15
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:03,240
Brother,

16
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:04,970
do you have a way?

17
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:07,080
Yes, do you want it?

18
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:10,090
Make it cheaper.

19
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,160
I can't, brother.

20
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:13,480
Not a penny less.

21
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:17,160
Brother, please donate for the War of Resistance.

22
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:19,640
Not a single penny.

23
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:25,329
Sir, please donate for the War of Resistance.

24
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:27,079
One gold bar.

25
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:29,360
Are you going to give it to me?

26
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:35,660
Hello. Please donate for the War of Resistance.

27
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:39,220
Hello. Please donate for the War of Resistance.

28
00:02:39,440 --> 00:02:40,720
Here, careful.

29
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:42,600
Here, water is coming.

30
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:43,720
Here.

31
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:46,760
Put it down.

32
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:48,560
Brother.

33
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:49,520
Give me a bucket of water.

34
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:50,440
Here, let me.

35
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:54,600
Move away.

36
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:55,520
I want some too.

37
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:56,160
Thank you.

38
00:02:56,440 --> 00:02:57,240
A little more.

39
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:58,160
Fill it up.

40
00:02:58,280 --> 00:02:59,800
Okay, that's enough.

41
00:03:00,040 --> 00:03:00,600
Here.

42
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:01,560
Zuliang.

43
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:03,440
Director Wang.

44
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:06,640
You students who joined the army on the front lines,

45
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:08,440
can't just work without eating.

46
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:09,440
We are not tired.

47
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:10,880
Right, we are not tired. We are fine.

48
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:11,960
The revolution is important,

49
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,440
but your health is equally important.

50
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:15,640
However, in view of your performance,

51
00:03:16,079 --> 00:03:17,600
the superiors have specially approved

52
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:20,280
the rank of Second Lieutenant for all of you.

53
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:22,850
Second Lieutenant!

54
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:23,760
Come and see.

55
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:27,680
Let me see.

56
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:28,880
Is it mine?

57
00:03:29,079 --> 00:03:30,280
This is a new uniform.

58
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:31,440
Is it ours?

59
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:33,360
My name is even written here.

60
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,880
Then I'll be a Second Lieutenant from now on.

61
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:35,880
You are too.

62
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:38,880
This looks so sharp.

63
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:40,050
How impressive.

64
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:41,440
We have some

65
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:43,800
new uniforms left in our warehouse,

66
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,930
consider it a bargain for you guys.

67
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:47,420
Director Wang.

68
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:49,320
Then we...

69
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:51,460
Try them on.

70
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,360
Let's go.

71
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:08,850
Come, let Daddy hug you.

72
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:12,970
Hold it well, it's warm.

73
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,519
Rock, paper, scissors.

74
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:18,519
Old man,

75
00:04:18,640 --> 00:04:20,170
do you want a foreign watch?

76
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:22,890
Look, it's elegant.

77
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:24,000
Go away.

78
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,200
Wait, I need to buy a ticket

79
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:26,840
to Hankou.

80
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,080
What are you doing here?

81
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,280
No money for a ticket.

82
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:31,080
Get out of here!

83
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:33,080
Write us a letter when you get there!

84
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:36,659
Newspapers! Newspapers!

85
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:40,040
Water for sale!

86
00:04:43,320 --> 00:04:45,480
Newspapers! Newspapers!

87
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:46,800
Excuse me,

88
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:50,540
Hold your luggage carefully. Watch out.

89
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:51,680
Excuse me.

90
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:53,000
Is the boat to Wuhan

91
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:54,340
checking tickets now?

92
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:56,610
There are no more boats to Wuhan today.

93
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:58,320
Have you seen a little brother,

94
00:04:58,320 --> 00:04:59,250
about this tall,

95
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:01,050
with a big patch on his clothes?

96
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:03,410
Your ticket is checked.

97
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:09,840
Please open the door!

98
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:11,480
Are there any tickets left?

99
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:12,520
What are you doing?

100
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:13,440
Stop!

101
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:20,120
I told you to stop!

102
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:24,160
Stop!

103
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:27,460
Don't think I can't catch you!

104
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,120
No rush.

105
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:31,040
Come, line up first.

106
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:32,300
Take out your tickets.

107
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,280
Hold your ticket.

108
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:46,040
Read the newspaper!

109
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:48,640
Brigade Commander Zhang Yunkui disobeyed orders.

110
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:51,280
Dachang is lost, the whole situation is trapped.

111
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:52,480
Newspapers!

112
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:54,280
Sir, newspaper.

113
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:56,320
Read the newspaper!

114
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:58,760
The entire 87th Brigade is held accountable.

115
00:05:58,760 --> 00:06:01,040
The runaway general is to blame.

116
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,640
Newspapers!

117
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,040
Brigade Commander Zhang Yunkui.

118
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:04,800
We will donate too.

119
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:05,480
Thank you for your support.

120
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:06,960
Kill a few more Japanese.

121
00:06:06,960 --> 00:06:07,480
Thank you.

122
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:09,810
Where did this runaway general come from?

123
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:12,440
Once Dachang is lost, everything is lost.

124
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:14,400
Sir,

125
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:16,200
the survival of the nation is at stake.

126
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:18,640
Please contribute to the war of resistance.

127
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:19,100
Donate.

128
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:19,720
Donate.

129
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:21,180
Thank you, sir.

130
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:22,680
Thank you, sir.

131
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:24,240
Thank you.

132
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:25,040
I'll donate too.

133
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:25,720
Thank you, ma'am.

134
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:26,960
We must support the war of resistance.

135
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:27,600
Thank you.

136
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:28,690
I'll donate too.

137
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:29,580
Thank you, sir.

138
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,200
Thank you for your support of the war of resistance.

139
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:31,760
Have to support it.

140
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:32,360
Thank you.

141
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:33,560
You are very righteous, sir.

142
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:34,840
China will win!

143
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,080
Thank you.

144
00:06:41,159 --> 00:06:41,880
Coward!

145
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:42,640
Traitor!

146
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:43,680
Traitor!

147
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:46,080
The Japanese haven't even arrived,

148
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:47,340
and you ran away first!

149
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:49,000
Leaving us civilians behind,

150
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,400
this is treason!

151
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:53,320
You!

152
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:54,040
Traitor!

153
00:06:54,159 --> 00:06:55,040
Defending the country,

154
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,360
is it worth doing this?

155
00:06:56,840 --> 00:06:57,240
Deserter!

156
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:58,159
You are a soldier.

157
00:06:58,159 --> 00:06:58,680
What are you doing?

158
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:00,210
You are paid by the country!

159
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:01,360
What kind of people are they?

160
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,360
Great-grandfather, let's go home.

161
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:04,480
I'll clean it up right away.

162
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:05,880
What a bunch of bastards.

163
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:07,600
Shut up!

164
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:09,760
Our young master is risking his life at the frontline,

165
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:11,360
protecting people like you.

166
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,060
You are the real traitors!

167
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:14,080
Your conscience

168
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:15,880
has been eaten by the Japs.

169
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,130
Don't you agree?

170
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:19,520
Don't tear it.

171
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:23,090
Whoever pasted it should tear it down.

172
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:27,360
Whoever threw it should clean it up

173
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:29,240
and apologize to me in person.

174
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:30,320
It's clearly written in the newspaper.

175
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:31,200
Great-grandfather,

176
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:32,260
still so stubborn.

177
00:07:32,440 --> 00:07:33,120
Shameless.

178
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:35,360
Where are you going, Great-grandfather?

179
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,840
Nationalist Government.

180
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:55,760
I thought you had already left the city.

181
00:07:58,480 --> 00:07:59,960
That high-ranking official,

182
00:07:59,960 --> 00:08:01,520
he pointed a gun at my head.

183
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,120
He threatened me,

184
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:05,890
saying I can never see the Zhang family again.

185
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,730
Of course I'm afraid to die.

186
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:09,960
I even got to the pier.

187
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:12,620
But as soon as I got there, I thought about it.

188
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:14,880
There must be something going on.

189
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:17,050
That official must be up to no good.

190
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,160
Then I remembered

191
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:22,040
our Brigade Commander saved my life.

192
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:24,320
I can't be that heartless.

193
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:30,320
Thank you, Brother Wanfu.

194
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:32,640
But that official,

195
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,600
he sounded so scary.

196
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:38,559
Come home with me.

197
00:08:39,159 --> 00:08:40,280
I will protect you.

198
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:42,850
I won't let them lay a finger on you.

199
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:13,680
Keep it straight.

200
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:16,960
Keep it straight.

201
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:25,300
It's been ten minutes.

202
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:27,480
Holding it for fifteen minutes without spilling a drop

203
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,740
is just too difficult.

204
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:31,740
The most important thing in surgery is steadiness.

205
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:32,760
Keep it straight.

206
00:10:13,560 --> 00:10:14,520
Brother Yunkui

207
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:16,080
is awake.

208
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:25,460
I'll go get him some porridge.

209
00:10:28,880 --> 00:10:30,320
Zuliang,

210
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,240
it's me, Brother Yunkui.

211
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:33,960
You saved me.

212
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:46,160
This is Liu Town.

213
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:48,690
This is the military hospital.

214
00:10:48,920 --> 00:10:50,380
I am a military doctor now.

215
00:10:54,760 --> 00:10:55,840
Dachang.

216
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,440
Dachang.

217
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:02,080
Dachang.

218
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:03,960
It's lost.

219
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:20,600
Brother Yunkui, you survived.

220
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:22,880
Don't think too much for now.

221
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:26,500
The doctor said you need to stay in bed for at least half a month.

222
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:38,680
You must tell me clearly

223
00:11:38,680 --> 00:11:39,080
Go.

224
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:40,140
what a deserter is.

225
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:41,480
Get out of here.

226
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:42,960
My son, Zhang Yunkui,

227
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:45,040
Zhang Yunkui is innocent!

228
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:47,930
We have both human and physical evidence.

229
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:48,640
Hurry up.

230
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:50,960
You can't just talk nonsense!

231
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:53,600
You all fled to the rear,

232
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:56,120
and Chairman Chiang also fled.

233
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:58,640
You are the real deserters!

234
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:02,120
My son died in battle on the Shanghai Battlefield,

235
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:04,040
and his body isn't even cold yet.

236
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:06,480
And you slander him in the newspapers!

237
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:08,920
You put the word 'deserter'

238
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:12,280
on soldiers who died in battle.

239
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:14,960
You are destroying his reputation after his death!

240
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:15,200
Go!

241
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:16,520
What are you two good for?

242
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:17,080
Drag him away.

243
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:17,610
Yes, sir.

244
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:19,640
You are destroying his reputation!

245
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:22,160
Liao Fengnian! Sun Huaiyi!

246
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:22,880
Madam.

247
00:12:22,880 --> 00:12:23,800
He Yingqin!

248
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:24,400
Great-grandfather is over there.

249
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:24,960
Dad.

250
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:26,200
Chiang Kai-shek!

251
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:27,400
Come out, all of you!

252
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:28,440
Great-grandfather!

253
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:29,880
I want to confront them!

254
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:32,280
Who is the fleeing general?

255
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:32,520
Great-grandfather.

256
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:34,200
Why did you come here, Dad?

257
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:36,520
Little brother,

258
00:12:36,920 --> 00:12:38,240
you're back.

259
00:12:38,920 --> 00:12:40,640
You came back at the right time.

260
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:41,360
I'm back.

261
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:43,250
I went to the Ministry of War

262
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:45,320
to seek justice for Yunkui,

263
00:12:45,680 --> 00:12:47,120
but they wouldn't let me in.

264
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:48,320
I could only come to

265
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:51,880
the highest Nationalist Government to appeal,

266
00:12:52,280 --> 00:12:54,640
but they still wouldn't let me in!

267
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,320
Look at these words.

268
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:58,680
Nationalist Government.

269
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,640
Whose nation are you?

270
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:02,340
Whose people do you serve?

271
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:04,000
Whose government are you?

272
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:05,920
Perfect.

273
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,240
We have a witness.

274
00:13:07,480 --> 00:13:08,280
Come in with me

275
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:09,960
and reason with them.

276
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:11,360
Great-grandfather.

277
00:13:11,360 --> 00:13:12,160
Dad, we can't go.

278
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:13,200
You can't.

279
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,880
Dad, look at this Nationalist Government.

280
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:16,680
It's already in such a mess.

281
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:18,920
They don't even know where they are going.

282
00:13:18,920 --> 00:13:20,980
What's the point of looking for them?

283
00:13:21,640 --> 00:13:21,840
Yujiao.

284
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:24,040
Even if you smash your head on the ground now,

285
00:13:24,040 --> 00:13:25,200
just like Yang Jiye

286
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:26,360
who hit his head on Li Ling's Stele,

287
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:28,480
no one will listen to you.

288
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:32,520
Yujiao,

289
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:35,320
this is Liao Fengnian's conspiracy.

290
00:13:35,640 --> 00:13:38,120
They suffered a crushing defeat on the front line,

291
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:39,320
and they put the blame

292
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:41,880
on our Yunkui.

293
00:13:42,280 --> 00:13:43,480
You said it yourself,

294
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:45,080
they intentionally put the blame

295
00:13:45,080 --> 00:13:46,360
on Yunkui.

296
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,400
Then why should we clash with them head-on?

297
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:53,480
Father, we can go to the newspaper.

298
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:55,200
They don't listen to us.

299
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:57,600
If we publish it, someone will listen.

300
00:13:57,880 --> 00:13:58,960
Let's use the power of public opinion

301
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:00,520
to clear Yunkui's name, okay?

302
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:01,320
Yes.

303
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:04,130
I can also testify for our Brigade Commander.

304
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:06,920
You are right.

305
00:14:07,120 --> 00:14:09,360
You are calmer than me.

306
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:11,250
They turn black into white,

307
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:13,090
committing countless crimes.

308
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:15,450
I will write a complaint when I go back.

309
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:18,080
I will send it to all the newspapers.

310
00:14:18,520 --> 00:14:20,640
I will announce it to the world.

311
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:21,920
Let's go back.

312
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:26,660
Nationalist Government.

313
00:14:26,920 --> 00:14:28,440
So big.

314
00:15:58,560 --> 00:16:01,240
Father, the meal is ready.

315
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:04,980
Where is Wanfu?

316
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:07,000
Here.

317
00:16:07,080 --> 00:16:08,610
It's good that you are here.

318
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:10,240
With you as a witness,

319
00:16:10,680 --> 00:16:12,200
there is still hope

320
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:13,720
for Yunkui's matter.

321
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:17,080
Yes.

322
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:19,640
Then Great-grandfather, let's eat.

323
00:16:19,640 --> 00:16:20,840
Before doing anything,

324
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:21,800
we must eat.

325
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:22,680
Come.

326
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:24,360
Let's eat.

327
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:29,480
Let me do it.

328
00:16:29,960 --> 00:16:30,890
I'm good at this.

329
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:32,760
We can't let the guest do it,

330
00:16:32,760 --> 00:16:34,040
it's the rule.

331
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:38,160
Wanfu.

332
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:40,640
What is China?

333
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,600
Great-grandfather,

334
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:46,800
you really stumped me.

335
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:48,400
Is it called China

336
00:16:50,040 --> 00:16:51,800
because we are in the middle?

337
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:52,920
Is that why?

338
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,460
We are the Chinese nation,

339
00:16:55,680 --> 00:16:58,480
including Han, Manchu, Mongol, Hui, and Tibetan.

340
00:16:58,880 --> 00:17:01,000
We share a common Chinese culture.

341
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:03,360
Well said.

342
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:06,920
Only culture

343
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:10,040
is the foundation of a nation.

344
00:17:11,599 --> 00:17:12,680
Not guns.

345
00:17:13,119 --> 00:17:14,400
Not emperors,

346
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,280
nor the name of the state.

347
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:18,579
Before the Republic of China,

348
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:21,800
China existed for five thousand years.

349
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:25,040
Through countless dynastic changes,

350
00:17:25,560 --> 00:17:27,760
culture has not died.

351
00:17:28,119 --> 00:17:31,680
It survives and continues.

352
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:34,760
This is culture.

353
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:38,280
Wanfu,

354
00:17:39,840 --> 00:17:41,200
do you understand?

355
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:43,480
No.

356
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:45,760
Great-grandfather,

357
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:46,960
I am a person

358
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,720
with no culture at all.

359
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:51,600
I barely know any words.

360
00:17:52,120 --> 00:17:53,120
No.

361
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:54,680
You do.

362
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:57,280
Culture is not about how many words you know,

363
00:17:57,280 --> 00:17:59,000
nor just about books.

364
00:17:59,440 --> 00:18:02,040
Culture is a thought of conscience.

365
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:04,000
Wanfu,

366
00:18:04,320 --> 00:18:06,560
you delivered the sword for Yunkui,

367
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:10,320
and risked your life to testify for him.

368
00:18:10,480 --> 00:18:13,320
This shows you have a conscience,

369
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,060
and a heart of compassion.

370
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:17,560
This is the culture of our nation.

371
00:18:19,440 --> 00:18:23,240
Yunkui is very lucky.

372
00:18:24,760 --> 00:18:28,720
To have a comrade and brother like you.

373
00:18:29,240 --> 00:18:30,920
Our Zhang family

374
00:18:34,560 --> 00:18:35,360
thanks you.

375
00:18:35,880 --> 00:18:37,000
Great-grandfather, please don't.

376
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:37,520
This...

377
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:38,640
Isn't this messing up the seniority?

378
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:40,280
How can we call each other brothers?

379
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:41,840
My father means

380
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,520
you and Yunkui are brothers.

381
00:18:46,760 --> 00:18:48,120
Then I and Brigade Commander Zhang

382
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:49,520
are naturally brothers.

383
00:18:50,520 --> 00:18:51,080
I

384
00:18:51,280 --> 00:18:52,480
vouch for my brother.

385
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:54,760
That's only right

386
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:56,640
and proper.

387
00:18:57,120 --> 00:18:58,520
It's what should be done.

388
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:10,200
Great-grandfather.

389
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:11,240
Come here.

390
00:19:11,480 --> 00:19:12,360
Actually,

391
00:19:13,080 --> 00:19:15,480
let me tell you the truth.

392
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:17,720
Please don't flatter me.

393
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,440
I really

394
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,440
can't stay here long.

395
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:30,040
It's like this.

396
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:31,600
I came back today

397
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:32,880
also because

398
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:35,200
I have to go to Wuhan.

399
00:19:35,760 --> 00:19:36,620
You don't know.

400
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:38,360
I have a fiancée.

401
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:39,520
She is in Wuhan now.

402
00:19:39,520 --> 00:19:41,850
She doesn't even know if I'm alive or dead.

403
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,600
I'm really afraid she isn't waiting for me anymore.

404
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:45,400
So I have to hurry over there.

405
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:46,940
But you don't know,

406
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:48,410
I went to the pier today.

407
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:49,810
The ticket price

408
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:51,240
changes every day.

409
00:19:51,360 --> 00:19:52,360
Every single day.

410
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:53,320
I...

411
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:54,440
the money in my pocket...

412
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:56,680
It's really

413
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:58,240
just

414
00:20:01,320 --> 00:20:02,440
not enough.

415
00:20:09,080 --> 00:20:10,400
Not enough.

416
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:21,120
Nurse,

417
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:23,240
we are reporters from the Anti-Enemy Backup Society.

418
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:24,920
We want to interview the wounded here,

419
00:20:24,920 --> 00:20:25,920
take some photos,

420
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:27,970
and publicize their heroic deeds.

421
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:29,970
Could you help introduce them?

422
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:31,440
Okay.

423
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:34,930
Squad Leader, Zhang Guifu.

424
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:36,800
He always charged at the front.

425
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:38,730
He's the best at bayonet fighting.

426
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:40,880
Come.

427
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:43,280
Three, two, one.

428
00:20:46,080 --> 00:20:48,120
Private First Class, Deng Guanghui.

429
00:20:48,120 --> 00:20:50,780
He was burned like this when saving the wounded.

430
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,960
One, two, three.

431
00:20:56,560 --> 00:20:57,960
Private, Yu Chengjie.

432
00:20:58,160 --> 00:21:00,290
He went to blow up tanks with grenades,

433
00:21:00,360 --> 00:21:01,480
both hands...

434
00:21:03,480 --> 00:21:04,680
Let's take a picture.

435
00:21:05,080 --> 00:21:06,160
Come.

436
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:08,960
Three, two, one.

437
00:21:09,280 --> 00:21:10,610
Company Commander Qin.

438
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:12,570
Company Commander Qin.

439
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:13,760
It's not lit.

440
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:15,920
You can enjoy it even without lighting it.

441
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:17,600
One puff and it won't hurt.

442
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:18,810
Have some water.

443
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:20,480
Water will help you.

444
00:21:22,920 --> 00:21:23,400
Thank you, Nurse.

445
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:25,360
Little kid.

446
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:00,680
Father,

447
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:03,780
Liao Fengnian sent someone to deliver this.

448
00:22:18,080 --> 00:22:19,240
What a villain.

449
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:21,960
He's two-faced and heartless.

450
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:24,720
It's entirely an excuse to stall and dodge.

451
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:33,680
The superiors have classified Yunkui

452
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:34,760
as absent without leave,

453
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:35,760
not as a deserter.

454
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:37,640
He blamed all the rights, wrongs, and problems

455
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:39,100
on the tabloid reporters,

456
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:42,320
saying they exaggerated.

457
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:44,960
He is obviously Yunkui's friend.

458
00:22:45,520 --> 00:22:47,520
He should have come forward to testify

459
00:22:47,520 --> 00:22:48,800
and stand up for him.

460
00:22:49,640 --> 00:22:52,770
Instead, he found an excuse to run back to the frontline.

461
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:54,320
This is unrighteous.

462
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:57,320
He's clearly a coward.

463
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:11,520
He also sent us

464
00:23:11,520 --> 00:23:13,240
three boat tickets to Wuhan.

465
00:23:13,960 --> 00:23:15,240
Petty favors.

466
00:23:16,320 --> 00:23:17,840
He is just trying to cover it up,

467
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:20,520
afraid I'll go make a scene at the Nanjing government.

468
00:23:20,520 --> 00:23:22,000
I cannot accept this.

469
00:23:26,560 --> 00:23:27,240
Father,

470
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:29,880
when Yunkui left, he told us

471
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:32,240
to be ready to go to Wuhan.

472
00:23:34,320 --> 00:23:36,960
Now, all the news from the frontline is bad.

473
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:39,560
Everyone in Nanjing is fleeing.

474
00:23:39,640 --> 00:23:40,760
You can also see

475
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:42,560
that the military and government officials

476
00:23:42,560 --> 00:23:43,920
are also retreating.

477
00:23:44,280 --> 00:23:46,440
Now, boat tickets from Nanjing to the rear

478
00:23:46,440 --> 00:23:47,770
change prices every day

479
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:49,280
and are hard to get.

480
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:51,400
If we miss this boat...

481
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:54,280
Yujiao.

482
00:23:55,240 --> 00:23:56,080
We can't be bought

483
00:23:56,080 --> 00:23:58,160
by these three boat tickets.

484
00:23:58,560 --> 00:24:00,440
Fleeing silently as refugees,

485
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:04,080
silently bearing Yunkui's injustice.

486
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:06,260
Nanjing has a million people,

487
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:08,040
they won't all run away.

488
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:11,080
If I don't clear Yunkui's name

489
00:24:11,240 --> 00:24:12,760
and wash away the injustice,

490
00:24:12,760 --> 00:24:15,020
I won't take a single step out of Nanjing.

491
00:24:16,520 --> 00:24:17,850
Liao Fengnian ran away,

492
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:19,250
and Sun Huaiyi ran away.

493
00:24:19,280 --> 00:24:20,720
I will use public opinion

494
00:24:20,720 --> 00:24:21,960
to seek justice.

495
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:24,320
I will submit articles to all the newspaper offices.

496
00:24:24,320 --> 00:24:25,760
I want to find a place

497
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:28,520
to get justice for Yunkui.

498
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:39,560
Yujiao.

499
00:24:40,080 --> 00:24:40,760
Dad.

500
00:24:40,760 --> 00:24:41,760
How about

501
00:24:42,120 --> 00:24:44,980
having Mrs. Liu accompany you back to our hometown?

502
00:24:46,320 --> 00:24:47,240
Dad.

503
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:51,520
When the war just started, Yunkui told me,

504
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:54,160
no matter what happens,

505
00:24:54,520 --> 00:24:56,520
our family shouldn't be separated.

506
00:24:56,800 --> 00:24:58,560
My parents died a long time ago.

507
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:01,570
Which hometown do you want me to return to?

508
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:07,120
You decide.

509
00:25:08,320 --> 00:25:09,720
I'll listen to you.

510
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:12,840
Okay.

511
00:25:15,640 --> 00:25:17,200
I'll continue writing.

512
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:42,680
Where is Wanfu?

513
00:25:47,080 --> 00:25:48,520
You don't know either.

514
00:25:57,680 --> 00:25:59,200
You don't know either.

515
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:14,600
Wanfu.

516
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:22,600
Where are you?

517
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:27,080
Mrs. Liu.

518
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:30,280
The three of the Yang family next door all left.

519
00:26:30,280 --> 00:26:32,120
They bought tickets from the black market.

520
00:26:32,120 --> 00:26:34,240
The situation is getting more tense by the day.

521
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:35,120
Master holds

522
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:36,680
3 tickets to Wuhan,

523
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:37,800
but he just won't leave.

524
00:26:37,800 --> 00:26:38,880
What should we do?

525
00:26:40,600 --> 00:26:42,840
Those Japanese planes come every day now.

526
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:43,720
When the alarm goes off,

527
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:44,520
where can you hide

528
00:26:44,520 --> 00:26:45,640
on a boat?

529
00:26:47,080 --> 00:26:49,000
Didn't you listen to the radio yesterday?

530
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:50,200
A boat in Jiujiang

531
00:26:50,360 --> 00:26:51,560
was bombed and sunk.

532
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:53,480
It's terrifying.

533
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:56,680
Yi.

534
00:26:57,440 --> 00:26:58,800
What do you think?

535
00:26:59,600 --> 00:27:00,320
Does it fit?

536
00:27:01,440 --> 00:27:02,400
Thank you.

537
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:05,800
Do you know

538
00:27:06,160 --> 00:27:07,640
the safest way to flee?

539
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:09,720
I don't know.

540
00:27:09,720 --> 00:27:10,720
By walking.

541
00:27:11,040 --> 00:27:13,120
And you must avoid highways and take small paths.

542
00:27:13,120 --> 00:27:14,780
Highways are too big a target.

543
00:27:15,320 --> 00:27:16,560
Have you ever seen a bombing?

544
00:27:16,560 --> 00:27:17,490
Of course I have.

545
00:27:17,920 --> 00:27:19,980
We run from air raid sirens every day.

546
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:21,880
Your running from sirens

547
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:23,040
is completely useless.

548
00:27:23,040 --> 00:27:24,570
It's not worth mentioning.

549
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:26,490
Let me tell you about it.

550
00:27:28,720 --> 00:27:29,640
Let me tell you,

551
00:27:30,800 --> 00:27:32,480
those Japanese planes.

552
00:27:33,160 --> 00:27:34,200
Look.

553
00:27:34,480 --> 00:27:35,410
With their wings

554
00:27:35,920 --> 00:27:36,920
tilted like this,

555
00:27:38,560 --> 00:27:40,080
they dive down

556
00:27:43,120 --> 00:27:44,800
and fly right over your scalp.

557
00:27:45,480 --> 00:27:46,360
You know?

558
00:27:46,680 --> 00:27:48,200
Then suddenly,

559
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:50,170
they pull up.

560
00:27:50,320 --> 00:27:52,000
They pull up and climb.

561
00:27:52,120 --> 00:27:53,240
Boom,

562
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:54,170
a bomb drops.

563
00:27:54,880 --> 00:27:55,880
Boom,

564
00:27:56,120 --> 00:27:57,250
a second bomb drops.

565
00:27:57,280 --> 00:27:58,680
Followed immediately by

566
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:02,960
a gust of hot wind,

567
00:28:04,160 --> 00:28:05,840
hitting you like a door.

568
00:28:06,760 --> 00:28:08,360
Then you can't see anything.

569
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:12,360
All you see is smoke and ash.

570
00:28:13,120 --> 00:28:15,640
Blood and torn flesh

571
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:18,160
fall all over you.

572
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:21,280
Let me tell you.

573
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:23,090
Nanjing was bombed,

574
00:28:23,320 --> 00:28:25,520
so Wuhan will definitely be bombed too.

575
00:28:25,960 --> 00:28:26,800
The Japanese.

576
00:28:27,280 --> 00:28:29,240
They specifically target crowded places.

577
00:28:29,240 --> 00:28:30,080
Big cities.

578
00:28:30,240 --> 00:28:32,240
Places with industry and commerce.

579
00:28:32,560 --> 00:28:34,420
Do you know where they don't bomb?

580
00:28:34,760 --> 00:28:35,490
I don't know.

581
00:28:36,520 --> 00:28:38,080
They don't bomb the countryside.

582
00:28:38,080 --> 00:28:39,120
What's the point of bombing

583
00:28:39,120 --> 00:28:40,000
a hole in a cabbage field?

584
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:41,240
Bombs cost money too.

585
00:28:42,200 --> 00:28:43,160
Exactly.

586
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:44,840
It's better to quit earlier

587
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:46,300
and go to the countryside.

588
00:28:46,400 --> 00:28:47,480
Yeah.

589
00:28:49,400 --> 00:28:50,280
Yi.

590
00:28:51,560 --> 00:28:52,360
Come and help.

591
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:53,640
Okay.

592
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:03,640
Yi.

593
00:29:04,240 --> 00:29:05,000
Do you know

594
00:29:05,400 --> 00:29:06,600
what it looks like when a piece of shrapnel

595
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:08,040
hits a head?

596
00:29:09,080 --> 00:29:10,320
Just like this.

597
00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:12,880
The white brains come pouring out.

598
00:29:13,280 --> 00:29:15,040
The worst is being shot in the stomach,

599
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:17,370
intestines spilling all over the ground.

600
00:29:18,760 --> 00:29:20,020
You are so disgusting.

601
00:29:27,960 --> 00:29:29,240
I can see

602
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:30,280
you

603
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:33,090
just want to scare Yi and me out of our wits,

604
00:29:33,280 --> 00:29:35,240
so we'll both be scared back to the countryside,

605
00:29:35,240 --> 00:29:36,080
right?

606
00:29:36,640 --> 00:29:38,560
You are coveting the Old Master's

607
00:29:38,560 --> 00:29:39,690
three boat tickets.

608
00:29:40,760 --> 00:29:42,820
What are you talking about, Mrs. Liu?

609
00:29:43,480 --> 00:29:45,960
I'm just telling Yi what I saw with my own eyes.

610
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:47,640
Don't be so petty.

611
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:49,840
I don't know if I'm petty or not.

612
00:29:49,840 --> 00:29:51,000
Let me be clear.

613
00:29:51,520 --> 00:29:52,760
I am all alone.

614
00:29:52,960 --> 00:29:54,520
I've been in the Zhang family for decades.

615
00:29:54,520 --> 00:29:56,050
The Zhang family is my home.

616
00:29:56,520 --> 00:29:58,400
Anyway, I will stick closely to Madam.

617
00:29:58,400 --> 00:30:00,000
Madam is about to give birth.

618
00:30:00,280 --> 00:30:01,000
I,

619
00:30:01,760 --> 00:30:02,640
no matter what,

620
00:30:03,200 --> 00:30:04,280
will never quit.

621
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:07,200
I won't quit.

622
00:30:30,960 --> 00:30:33,200
Father, you're back.

623
00:30:38,080 --> 00:30:39,640
If you don't eat a bite,

624
00:30:39,880 --> 00:30:41,740
your body won't be able to take it.

625
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:46,520
Let me go heat it up for you.

626
00:30:46,520 --> 00:30:48,320
You should eat at least a little.

627
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:50,520
Yujiao.

628
00:30:51,560 --> 00:30:52,840
Sit down.

629
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:11,800
My son Yunkui, courtesy name Xingwu,

630
00:31:12,680 --> 00:31:15,120
a native of Haiwen, Jiangsu,

631
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:19,280
born in the 31st year of Guangxu.

632
00:31:19,560 --> 00:31:21,360
He lost his mother at six,

633
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:23,960
but always strove to be strong.

634
00:31:24,680 --> 00:31:26,360
You died,

635
00:31:26,680 --> 00:31:28,940
and I could not bring you home for burial.

636
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:30,600
Your name is disgraced,

637
00:31:30,880 --> 00:31:33,200
and I have nowhere to clear your name.

638
00:31:34,200 --> 00:31:35,480
You gallantly

639
00:31:35,920 --> 00:31:37,240
died for our country.

640
00:31:38,080 --> 00:31:41,080
Yet I hesitate, not knowing whether to stay or go.

641
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:44,640
Alas, the court has lost its way,

642
00:31:45,280 --> 00:31:47,010
with wolves blocking the path.

643
00:31:47,320 --> 00:31:49,080
They shirked their duties

644
00:31:49,360 --> 00:31:52,440
and made you bear the blame and execution.

645
00:31:53,280 --> 00:31:54,120
Sorrow!

646
00:31:54,160 --> 00:31:56,890
No sorrow is greater than a father losing his son.

647
00:31:57,560 --> 00:31:58,480
Hatred!

648
00:31:58,480 --> 00:31:59,810
No hatred is deeper than

649
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:01,620
the strong bullying the weak.

650
00:32:02,120 --> 00:32:04,000
Black and white are reversed

651
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:05,560
by those in power.

652
00:32:05,760 --> 00:32:07,680
Right and wrong are blurred

653
00:32:07,800 --> 00:32:08,880
for the commoners.

654
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:11,520
Oh, heaven above,

655
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:13,480
why did you kill my good man?

656
00:32:14,360 --> 00:32:15,640
Two months ago,

657
00:32:16,320 --> 00:32:18,580
you brought me medicine before you left.

658
00:32:19,040 --> 00:32:20,840
Your earnest tugging at my clothes

659
00:32:20,840 --> 00:32:22,640
is still vivid in my mind.

660
00:32:23,280 --> 00:32:28,360
I still look up to Yan Zhenqing and Zheng Banqiao.

661
00:32:29,360 --> 00:32:30,840
Rivers are wide and deep,

662
00:32:31,640 --> 00:32:33,370
deer and apes gather together.

663
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:37,840
Oh, souls, feel no sorrow or fear.

664
00:32:38,720 --> 00:32:43,080
But your wife is expecting and hasn't given birth to a son yet.

665
00:32:44,080 --> 00:32:46,520
How dare I die?

666
00:32:46,760 --> 00:32:47,840
Alas,

667
00:32:48,120 --> 00:32:51,520
if you have a spirit, could you tell me?

668
00:32:53,240 --> 00:32:56,600
Alas, it hurts!

669
00:32:56,880 --> 00:32:59,560
Alas, it hurts!

670
00:33:05,360 --> 00:33:08,640
Today I will send it to the 'Central Daily News'.

671
00:33:09,200 --> 00:33:10,730
If they dare not publish it,

672
00:33:10,760 --> 00:33:12,480
I will print a few more copies,

673
00:33:12,920 --> 00:33:14,780
'Morning Post', 'Evening News'.

674
00:33:14,920 --> 00:33:15,760
I don't believe

675
00:33:15,760 --> 00:33:18,120
there is no place to reason in Nanjing.

676
00:33:40,800 --> 00:33:41,720
Yi,

677
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:44,240
are you really running back to your hometown in the country?

678
00:33:44,240 --> 00:33:46,120
Don't listen to Wanfu trying to scare you.

679
00:33:46,120 --> 00:33:47,680
There are only three boat tickets.

680
00:33:47,680 --> 00:33:49,540
I'd better go back to the country.

681
00:33:53,280 --> 00:33:54,400
Slow down.

682
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:56,080
Let me help.

683
00:33:56,080 --> 00:33:57,120
No need.

684
00:34:00,160 --> 00:34:01,240
Mrs. Liu,

685
00:34:01,600 --> 00:34:02,520
I need to discuss something with you.

686
00:34:02,520 --> 00:34:03,360
No.

687
00:34:03,960 --> 00:34:04,840
I haven't said anything yet,

688
00:34:04,840 --> 00:34:06,500
and you're already saying no?

689
00:34:06,760 --> 00:34:07,320
No.

690
00:34:07,520 --> 00:34:08,679
I...

691
00:34:10,199 --> 00:34:11,159
Madam.

692
00:34:12,159 --> 00:34:14,840
Great-grandfather hasn't eaten anything at all.

693
00:34:14,840 --> 00:34:16,170
I'll go heat it up again.

694
00:34:16,600 --> 00:34:17,480
Yi,

695
00:34:18,040 --> 00:34:19,719
bring those two dishes over too,

696
00:34:19,719 --> 00:34:20,880
I'll heat them up together.

697
00:34:20,880 --> 00:34:21,440
Here.

698
00:34:25,960 --> 00:34:27,080
I see,

699
00:34:27,400 --> 00:34:29,199
these two share the same temper.

700
00:34:29,520 --> 00:34:30,780
Madam, you don't know.

701
00:34:30,840 --> 00:34:32,159
When we were on the battlefield,

702
00:34:32,159 --> 00:34:34,239
our Brigade Commander was either looking at the map,

703
00:34:34,239 --> 00:34:35,199
thinking about things,

704
00:34:35,199 --> 00:34:36,460
or making phone calls.

705
00:34:36,679 --> 00:34:38,480
He'd be busy for days and nights,

706
00:34:38,719 --> 00:34:40,380
and he wouldn't eat anything.

707
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:41,639
So he got internal heat,

708
00:34:41,639 --> 00:34:43,560
and his mouth was full of blisters.

709
00:34:43,560 --> 00:34:45,820
Later, I used winter melon and mung beans

710
00:34:46,040 --> 00:34:48,500
to make him a cooling soup to reduce the heat.

711
00:34:48,560 --> 00:34:50,159
Our Brigade Commander actually finished it all

712
00:34:50,159 --> 00:34:51,520
and praised how good it tasted.

713
00:34:51,520 --> 00:34:54,179
How about I make one for Great-grandfather too?

714
00:34:54,280 --> 00:34:56,400
By the way, I'll use this winter melon and dried shrimp

715
00:34:56,400 --> 00:34:58,800
to make him a big stuffed Bun.

716
00:34:59,320 --> 00:35:00,240
Oh my goodness,

717
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:02,020
you can also make Buns?

718
00:35:02,120 --> 00:35:03,400
What did you think?

719
00:35:03,600 --> 00:35:04,600
During the Mid-Autumn Festival,

720
00:35:04,600 --> 00:35:05,440
I was on the battlefield,

721
00:35:05,440 --> 00:35:06,840
and I used water caltrops

722
00:35:07,040 --> 00:35:08,920
to make water caltrop mooncakes for our Brigade Commander.

723
00:35:08,920 --> 00:35:09,680
He praised me,

724
00:35:09,680 --> 00:35:13,010
saying it was even better than the ones from Guanshengyuan.

725
00:35:15,280 --> 00:35:16,200
Don't.

726
00:35:22,680 --> 00:35:25,140
Great-grandfather still refuses to leave?

727
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:29,800
He's been writing letters of appeal,

728
00:35:29,800 --> 00:35:32,480
but I went out looking for newspapers today.

729
00:35:33,600 --> 00:35:36,600
'Central Daily News' has already withdrawn to Wuhan.

730
00:35:37,560 --> 00:35:38,880
'Nanjing People's Daily'

731
00:35:38,880 --> 00:35:40,280
and other newspaper offices,

732
00:35:40,280 --> 00:35:41,400
have either suspended publication

733
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:43,130
or simply have no one in charge.

734
00:35:43,720 --> 00:35:45,440
Actually, no matter how much he writes,

735
00:35:45,440 --> 00:35:47,240
there's nowhere to submit them.

736
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:49,480
But seeing him like that today,

737
00:35:49,560 --> 00:35:51,600
I really don't know how to tell him.

738
00:35:53,760 --> 00:35:54,680
All right.

739
00:35:54,880 --> 00:35:55,740
Take your time.

740
00:35:56,880 --> 00:35:57,880
Madam.

741
00:35:58,720 --> 00:35:59,520
How about

742
00:36:00,040 --> 00:36:02,170
I try to persuade Great-grandfather?

743
00:36:02,840 --> 00:36:03,960
Do you have a way?

744
00:36:04,520 --> 00:36:05,360
Let me try.

745
00:36:05,600 --> 00:36:07,930
What if Great-grandfather listens to me?

746
00:36:09,360 --> 00:36:11,600
If you can persuade Great-grandfather,

747
00:36:11,600 --> 00:36:13,000
that would be wonderful.

748
00:36:14,520 --> 00:36:15,560
Then Madam,

749
00:36:16,120 --> 00:36:18,050
if I persuade Great-grandfather,

750
00:36:19,160 --> 00:36:20,720
can I make a small request?

751
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:21,600
No.

752
00:36:21,960 --> 00:36:22,640
No.

753
00:36:23,920 --> 00:36:24,880
No.

754
00:36:25,040 --> 00:36:26,720
Then Madam, if not, I'll leave.

755
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:27,280
Go.

756
00:36:27,440 --> 00:36:28,160
Wanfu,

757
00:36:29,600 --> 00:36:30,560
let him speak.

758
00:36:34,680 --> 00:36:35,360
Madam,

759
00:36:35,600 --> 00:36:38,460
if I can persuade Great-grandfather to go to Wuhan,

760
00:36:38,960 --> 00:36:40,290
can you take me with you?

761
00:36:40,680 --> 00:36:41,240
No,

762
00:36:41,400 --> 00:36:42,240
I know

763
00:36:42,480 --> 00:36:44,880
I shouldn't make requests for helping you.

764
00:36:45,040 --> 00:36:46,200
But Madam, you don't know,

765
00:36:46,200 --> 00:36:48,520
the price of a boat ticket to Wuhan these days

766
00:36:48,520 --> 00:36:50,280
is more than selling me three or four times over.

767
00:36:50,280 --> 00:36:51,760
I'm worried sick.

768
00:36:55,640 --> 00:36:56,640
Alright.

769
00:36:57,280 --> 00:36:59,720
If you can persuade Great-grandfather to go to Wuhan,

770
00:36:59,720 --> 00:37:00,760
we'll take you.

771
00:37:01,960 --> 00:37:03,240
Thank you, Madam.

772
00:37:03,760 --> 00:37:04,960
Then

773
00:37:05,760 --> 00:37:08,560
I'll make some buns for Great-grandfather first.

774
00:37:08,920 --> 00:37:09,960
Mrs. Liu,

775
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:12,240
can you help me out?

776
00:37:19,280 --> 00:37:20,240
Alright.

777
00:37:20,760 --> 00:37:22,220
Go slice the winter melon.

778
00:37:25,120 --> 00:37:26,400
I'll go now.

779
00:38:14,120 --> 00:38:19,600
Who caused this disaster?

780
00:38:20,080 --> 00:38:23,810
Heaven does not repent of the disaster. Who caused this suffering?

781
00:38:24,040 --> 00:38:24,960
Read 'Tu'.

782
00:38:27,840 --> 00:38:30,970
This is Yan Zhenqing's 'Draft of a Requiem to My Nephew'.

783
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:34,260
You don't eat or drink.

784
00:38:34,840 --> 00:38:36,480
You don't hide from the alarms.

785
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:38,740
So you're practicing calligraphy here.

786
00:38:41,280 --> 00:38:42,400
What's the use

787
00:38:43,560 --> 00:38:45,240
of saying these things?

788
00:38:51,240 --> 00:38:52,970
Can this shoot down airplanes?

789
00:39:09,280 --> 00:39:11,440
I'm not afraid to tell you the truth.

790
00:39:11,760 --> 00:39:12,720
You

791
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:14,680
are the most muddled

792
00:39:15,120 --> 00:39:17,640
and ungrateful person I've ever met.

793
00:39:21,240 --> 00:39:22,640
Why are you glaring at me?

794
00:39:23,160 --> 00:39:23,760
I'm afraid of guns and bullets,

795
00:39:23,760 --> 00:39:25,000
and I'm afraid of you glaring at me.

796
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:26,960
If you have a great grievance,

797
00:39:27,240 --> 00:39:29,040
you should appeal it.

798
00:39:29,400 --> 00:39:31,120
You should curse.

799
00:39:31,840 --> 00:39:33,120
Just being a bully at home.

800
00:39:33,120 --> 00:39:35,720
Who are you scaring by not eating and drinking?

801
00:39:35,720 --> 00:39:37,120
All talk and no action.

802
00:39:37,360 --> 00:39:38,960
I don't see you really cursing.

803
00:39:38,960 --> 00:39:40,440
If you really want to curse,

804
00:39:40,440 --> 00:39:42,640
you have to let the right person hear it.

805
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:44,400
I heard on the radio

806
00:39:44,840 --> 00:39:46,240
that the military and political officials

807
00:39:46,240 --> 00:39:48,000
have all moved to Wuhan.

808
00:39:48,440 --> 00:39:49,960
The main person has gone to Wuhan.

809
00:39:49,960 --> 00:39:52,160
You have to chase him to Wuhan and curse.

810
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:57,490
We'll chase them and curse.

811
00:39:57,720 --> 00:40:00,200
Wherever they go, we'll curse.

812
00:40:00,400 --> 00:40:01,440
I'll help you curse.

813
00:40:01,440 --> 00:40:03,440
Who is loyal and who is treacherous,

814
00:40:03,440 --> 00:40:05,160
we must say it clearly

815
00:40:05,160 --> 00:40:06,000
and plainly.

816
00:40:06,200 --> 00:40:08,200
Otherwise, what does the storytelling say?

817
00:40:08,200 --> 00:40:08,880
That...

818
00:40:09,080 --> 00:40:09,840
That play...

819
00:40:09,880 --> 00:40:10,680
That one...

820
00:40:10,800 --> 00:40:12,600
The one where he cursed Cao Cao naked...

821
00:40:12,600 --> 00:40:13,520
What's it called?

822
00:40:13,520 --> 00:40:15,720
Mi Zhengping Curses the Thief Naked.

823
00:40:17,480 --> 00:40:18,880
That doesn't seem right.

824
00:40:19,120 --> 00:40:20,200
Called...

825
00:40:20,360 --> 00:40:21,420
What was it called?

826
00:40:24,120 --> 00:40:25,980
Beating the Drum and Cursing Cao.

827
00:40:26,280 --> 00:40:27,360
Great-grandfather,

828
00:40:27,360 --> 00:40:28,120
if Chairman Jiang

829
00:40:28,120 --> 00:40:30,040
doesn't clear our Brigade Commander's name,

830
00:40:30,040 --> 00:40:31,320
then he is Cao Cao.

831
00:40:31,760 --> 00:40:32,840
Then we have to do

832
00:40:33,560 --> 00:40:36,200
a 'Beating the Drum and Cursing Jiang'.

833
00:40:47,400 --> 00:40:50,280
Teach you treacherous dog a lesson,

834
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:54,760
you will die without a good end.

835
00:40:57,040 --> 00:40:59,000
Pack my bags,

836
00:40:59,120 --> 00:41:01,640
travel by night,

837
00:41:02,280 --> 00:41:05,680
and go to Jingzhou.

838
00:41:06,960 --> 00:41:10,400
Wuhan, cursing Jiang.

839
00:41:25,160 --> 00:41:26,320
Zuliang, Zuliang.

840
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:28,080
Where can I make a phone call?

841
00:41:28,080 --> 00:41:29,940
I need to call the Ministry of War.

842
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:31,640
Since you can get out of bed,

843
00:41:31,640 --> 00:41:32,640
tomorrow at dawn,

844
00:41:32,840 --> 00:41:33,700
you must leave.

845
00:41:33,960 --> 00:41:35,520
I've altered your registration at the hospital.

846
00:41:35,520 --> 00:41:36,120
Remember,

847
00:41:36,440 --> 00:41:37,480
you've never been here.

848
00:41:37,480 --> 00:41:38,880
And I've never saved you.

849
00:41:40,080 --> 00:41:41,040
What do you mean?

850
00:41:41,640 --> 00:41:42,440
Dr. Luo.

851
00:41:42,720 --> 00:41:44,850
Is the medicine for patient 158 ready?

852
00:41:46,640 --> 00:41:47,440
I understand.

853
00:41:47,600 --> 00:41:48,320
In the end,

854
00:41:48,520 --> 00:41:49,880
everyone wants to save their own life.

855
00:41:49,880 --> 00:41:51,240
Our hospital received orders

856
00:41:51,240 --> 00:41:52,720
to be ready to retreat at any time.

857
00:41:52,720 --> 00:41:53,920
A platoon from the military police will come

858
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:54,680
to assist us.

859
00:41:55,160 --> 00:41:56,640
Don't tell anyone

860
00:41:56,760 --> 00:41:57,440
who you are.

861
00:41:57,680 --> 00:41:59,080
What exactly is going on?

862
00:42:03,360 --> 00:42:04,200
See for yourself.
